Questions:
What is the primary goal of the PROMOTE Pilot Study?
A) To evaluate the effectiveness of a new blood pressure medication in pharmacies;
B) To assess the impact of pharmacy staff training on the sale of over-the-counter medications;
C) To understand pharmacy staff perspectives on delivering HPV vaccinations to children in pharmacies;
D) To compare different brands of HPV vaccines for effectiveness.

Correct answer: C

Which of the following is considered the experimental procedure in the PROMOTE Pilot Study?
A) Completing standard surveys about pharmacy practices;
B) Attending regular staff meetings at the pharmacy;
C) Implementing a new communication strategy for promoting HPV vaccinations;
D) Providing routine HPV vaccinations to patients.

Correct answer: C

If you decide not to participate in the PROMOTE Pilot Study, what is an alternative option available to you?
A) You will be required to attend the training sessions without participating in the study; 
B) You will not have any alternative options and must participate in the study; 
C) You can continue your usual pharmacy practice without employing the new communication strategy; 
D) You will be automatically enrolled in a different study related to HPV vaccination.

Correct answer: C
